WHAT'S CHANGEDJazz Pharmaceuticals PLC (JAZZ.O)FromPrice Target$162.00

Jazz hosted an investor call following the Aug 6 accelerated approval of Modesyo. Clarity provided on the market access strategy led us to adjust our price & market penetration assumptions, which resulted in a small increase to our price target.

Modesyo launches at \(\) 32k\(/bottle, targeting H3 K27M - mutant glioma.\) \ \(832k\) annual list price for adults; pediatric pricing varies. Uptake expected mainly in academic centers due to biopsy needs. Phase 3 trial ongoing; over half of 450 patients enrolled. Price target adjusted to \(\) 163\(due to increased sales projection.

Modesyo (dordaviprone) launches with a \(\) 32k\(/bottle list price. Modesyo represents the first FDA approved targeted therapy H3 K27M - mutant Diffuse Midline Glioma. On the call, a leading Director of an academic NeuroOncology center highlighted the clinical needs in H3 K27M glioma, where radiation is still standard of care in 1L. With a 1 year median OS from diagnosis (or \(\sim 6\) months from recurrence), improved options are needed for the \(\sim 2k\) annual incident patient population, and in the Phase 2 results, the KOL emphasized the \(35\%\) 24- month OS (Exhibit 1). Of note, validating H3 K27 mutation requires biopsy, and as a result of the challenging tumor location near thalamus and midline, Modesyo uptake is expected to be largely restricted to academic centers. On the call, the company announced a \(\) 32k\(list price per 10 - 125mg capsules two week supply (dosed at 625 mg orally once - weekly), implying an\) \ \(832k\) annual list price ( \(32k*52\) weeks/2) for adults. For pediatric, Modesyo is available via weight- based dosing (Exhibit 2), implying \(\) 32k\(blended list price across pediatrics and adults, and the company guided - to exclusivity out to 2037 with potential for pediatric term extension.

Phase 3 1L ACTION trial is ongoing, as are plans for EMA submission. More than half of the 450 patients expected have already enrolled in the study evaluating Modesyo as once weekly or twice weekly vs. placebo. Earlier this year, the company paused domestic study enrollment to prevent confounding of cross- over placebo switch arm ( \(95+\) ex- US sites open), and will update timelines for its domestic sites at a later date.

Model updates: We adjusted our Modesyo list price to \(\) 832K\(from\) \ \(850k\) However, given pediatric mix (we assume half of patient, at \(60\%\) equivalent dose or \(375mg\) ), we model \(80\%\) effective list price, or \(\) 665K\(list. The net result is that our peak Modesyo sales go to\) \ \(389M\) (from \(\) 271M\(and our PT goes to\) \ \(163\) (from \(\) 162\$

We forecast \(\sim\) 1.95bn in peak oxybate franchise sales with combined residual sales of \(\) 11.4bn\(post - 2027 LOE. We see meaningful expansion opportunity for Zihera beyond biliary tract cancer into gastroesophageal adenocarcinoma. Balance sheet strategy/business development execution is critical to support the terminal value.

Further growth comes from additional encouraging pipeline updates, and Zihera drives oncology sales growth with \(\sim\) 1.5B in peak risk- adjusted revenues.

Jazz reaches \(\sim\) 5B in peak annual revenues. Xyrem franchise conversion to low- sodium Xyraw remains stable and Epidiolex continues to grow. Zihera contributes to oncology sales growth with \(\sim\) 1B in peak risk- adjusted revenues.

Jazz product sales show slowing growth, driven by oxybate pressure. Additional narcolepsy & cataplexy market competitive threats are more troubling than anticipated. Epidiolex sales are lower than expected, and Zihera has limited market uptake, resulting in balance sheet pressures.
